summary: An ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 26929, entitled: "An ordinance providing for the laying off, opening, widening, extending and establishing of a public street and highway across a portion of the north half of section 16, township 25 north, range 4 east, W.M.; providing for the condemnation, appropriation, taking and damaging of land and other property necessary therefor and providing that the cost of said improvement shall be paid by special assessment upon the property specially benefited in the manner provided by law", approved April 3, 1911, approved April 11, 1911, and authorizing the dismissal of the action in the Superior Court of King County, Washington, based upon said ordinance; setting aside the judgement in said case and authorizing the payment of all taxable costs.
